            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the orzo has been cooking for 5 min, add the<strong> halved green beans</strong> and cook, covered, for a further 10 min or until the beans are tender with a slight bite and the chicken is cooked through (no pink meat!)</p><p>Tip: Add a splash more water if your orzo is looking a little dry, and stir it occasionally to prevent it from sticking!</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1687248453477-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1687248453477-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1687248453477-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1687248453477-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1687248453477-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once done, add a large knob of<strong> butter</strong>, the juice of <strong>half</strong> your<strong> lemon[s]</strong> and a very generous grind of <strong>black pepper</strong></p><p>Wash your <strong>spinach </strong>and pat dry with kitchen paper, then add it to the pan<strong> </strong>and cook for a further 2-3 min or until wilted</p><p>Add <strong>half</strong> of your <strong>grated Italian hard cheese</strong> (save the rest for garnish!) and give everything a good mix up – this is your <strong>chicken breast orzo primavera</strong></p><p>Cut the <strong>remaining</strong> <strong>lemon</strong> into 1 wedge per person</p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1687248456187-x200.jpg",
